Package: assetIS
Type: Package
Title: Importance Sampling for ASSET Tail Probability Estimation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Samuel",
                  family = "Anyaso-Samuel",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "samuel.anyaso-samuel@nih.gov",
                  comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Provides efficient importance sampling (IS) estimators of tail
    probabilities for the ASSET subset-based meta-analysis statistic
    (Bhattacharjee et al., 2012). Naive Monte Carlo estimation of extreme
    tail probabilities is computationally prohibitive; the IS estimators in
    this package use exponential tilting to concentrate simulation effort
    in the target region, achieving large variance reductions. Four
    estimators are provided covering the factorial combination of two
    design dimensions: (i) Gaussian versus non-Gaussian (discrete genotype)
    settings, and (ii) independent versus correlated study-level score
    statistics. The Gaussian estimators are suitable for large-sample
    continuous-trait meta-analysis; the non-Gaussian estimators are designed
    for settings where normality fails, including single-cell eQTL mapping
    across cell types and meta-analysis of rare diseases with small to
    moderate sample sizes. All estimators support one- and two-sided
    p-values, vectorised threshold evaluation via a range approximation,
    case-control studies (with effective sample sizes or direct binary
    outcome matrices), covariate adjustment, multi-ancestry analyses with
    study-specific allele frequencies, and optional parallel computation.
